== 分版 ==
=== /a/ ===
/a/版（Anime and Manga，日本動畫與漫畫）是4chan上專門討論日本動漫文化的貼圖版。<ref name=rulesib>{{cite web|url=http://www.4chan.org/rules#imgboard|title=4chan rules: Image Boards|website=4chan|language=en}}</ref><!--在英文世界裡的動畫[[字幕組|字幕組]]交流中，/a/版是非常有影響力的。許多字幕组使用/a/、博客和[[IRC|IRC]]發布公告和討論。-->/a/的版民常討論的內容有目前正播的日本動畫、美少女塑料模型、共享漫畫圖片。/a/版是全4chan上最老的討論區。<ref name=2011japaninterview/><ref name=TechRev/>在英文世界裡的動畫圈中，/a/版是非常有影響力的——版上偶爾出現過各樣的[[輕小說|輕小說]]作家來訪問。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2013-12-07/log-horizon-creator-holds-q&a-on-4chan/a/board|title=Log Horizon Creator Holds Q&A on 4Chan's /a/ Board|date=2013-12-08|website=[[Anime_News_Network|Anime News Network]]|language=en|accessdate=2020-09-24|archive-date=2017-07-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170731061308/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2013-12-07/log-horizon-creator-holds-q%26a-on-4chan/a/board|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2013/12/07/log-horizon-author-returns-to-4chan|title="Log Horizon" Author Returns to 4Chan|date=2013-12-08|website=[[Crunchyroll|Crunchyroll]]|language=en|accessdate=2015-09-16|archive-date=2015-04-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150416052215/http://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2013/12/07/log-horizon-author-returns-to-4chan|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== /b/ ===
/b/版（Random，隨機版）是4chan上最流行的貼圖版，占据全網站30%的流量。網站推出時，/b/版是4chan第一个創建的貼圖版，原始目标就是仿照2chan的「二次元裏」版設計版块。<ref>{{cite web | url = http://fimoculous.com/archive/post-5738.cfm | title = An Interview With The Founder of 4chan | last = Sorgatz | first = Rex | publisher = Fimoculous.com | date = 2009-02-18 | accessdate = 2009-05-18 | language = en | archive-date = 2009-07-10 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20090710113640/http://www.fimoculous.com/archive/post-5738.cfm | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.4chan.org/news.php?all#101|title=/b/|publisher=4chan|author=moot|date=2008-07-11|accessdate=2008-07-14|language=en|archive-date=2013-06-30|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6HlmWN8qm?url=http://www.4chan.org/news?all#101|dead-url=no}}</ref>/b/版有一個「no rules」（沒有規則）的方針：除了違法內容以外（如兒童色情物品和發垃圾郵件），什麼都可以貼。 「no rules」方針所针对的也包括管理員的管理行为，也即使用者亦可以在任何时候以任何理由——甚至沒理由——被封禁。<ref name=transcript/><ref name="4chanTOS">{{cite web| url=http://www.4chan.org/rules.php#b|title=4chan — Rules – /b/ - Random|publisher=4chan|accessdate=2006-08-18|language=en}}</ref>在一次《[[紐約時報|紐約時報]]》的采访中，克里斯托弗·普尔表示在/b/版中：「版民的力量在於：以自己的標準来決定」，管理員只是担当平台提供者而已。<ref name="nyt">{{cite news|last=Schwartz|first=Mattathias|title=The Trolls Among Us|work=[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]|page=24|date=2008-08-03|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2008/08/03/magazine/03trolls-t.html|accessdate=2009-01-11|language=en|archive-date=2018-07-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180707035850/https://www.nytimes.com/2008/08/03/magazine/03trolls-t.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

/b/版的特點是錯綜複雜的內部笑話和黑色喜劇。<ref name="Wired">{{cite web| url = http://www.wired.com/gaming/virtualworlds/magazine/16-02/mf_goons?currentPage=all| title = Mutilated Furries, Flying Phalluses: Put the Blame on Griefers| author = Julian Dibbell| work = [[连线|连线]]| date = 2008-01-18| accessdate = 2008-01-18| language = en| archive-date = 2008-07-08| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20080708052552/http://www.wired.com/gaming/virtualworlds/magazine/16-02/mf_goons?currentPage=all| dead-url = no}}</ref>/b/版的用戶自称「/b/tards」（/b/精神病人）<!--{{notetag|参见英文维基词典条目[[wikt:en:retard|retard]]}}-->，<ref name="nyt"/>这是外來人往往難以理解的一種很特別的幽默感；而用戶亦常把其他用戶叫成「fags」（同性戀的傢伙），<ref name="landers" />因而外來人容易把他們看成[[白目|白目]]。<ref name="nyt" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nationalpost.com/opinion/columnists/story.html?id=94f40e62-2db2-4917-8e21-e17b9a25b2db&p=1|title=You'll miss us when we're gone|publisher=[[National_Post|National Post]]|author=Jonathan Kay|date=2008-08-06|accessdate=2008-08-06|language=en|archive-url=https://archive.is/20120905013138/http://www.nationalpost.com/opinion/columnists/story.html?id=94f40e62-2db2-4917-8e21-e17b9a25b2db&p=1|archive-date=2012-09-05|dead-url=yes}}</ref>《[[纽约观察家|纽约观察家]]》周刊把/b/的用戶描述为「不成熟的惡作劇者，而網站的匿名與无存檔机制也鼓励了他们的不良行為」。<ref name=Jeffries>{{Cite news|url=http://www.observer.com/2011/tech/creator-4chan-comes-more-mature-canvas?utm_source=observer&utm_medium=internal_links&utm_campaign=slider|title=From the Creator of 4chan Comes the More Mature Canvas|first=Adrianne|last=Jeffries|journal=[[纽约观察家|纽约观察家]]|date=2011-01-31|accessdate=2011-02-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110204222852/http://www.observer.com/2011/tech/creator-4chan-comes-more-mature-canvas?utm_source=observer&utm_medium=internal_links&utm_campaign=slider|archive-date=2011-02-04|language=en|dead-url=yes}}</ref>Gawker.com的尼克·道格拉斯甚至写道「看/b/會把你的大腦給融化掉……（/b/是）互联網的屁眼」（{{lang|en|reading /b/ will melt your brain... the asshole of the Internets}}）<ref name="Gawker" />《[[連線|連線]]》雜誌则以「臭名昭著」（「notorious」）相称。<ref name="Wired" />

=== /v/ ===
/v/版（Video Games，电子游戏）是討論電腦與电子游戏的貼圖版。<ref name=rulesib/>/v/上的管理員經常鬆懈，因此版民常常討論無關的話題，一個由此衍生出的很常見的/v/版玩笑是「/v/ never talks about video games（/v/版从不討論電子遊戲）」。<ref name=2011japaninterview/>由于很多人因在/v/上帖關於[[口袋妖怪系列|口袋妖怪系列]]的信息而被其他版民騷擾，克里斯托弗·普尔在2010年新創建了專門討論口袋妖怪的/vp/版，並於2012年將/v/版分割出一般討論相关遊戲系列专用的/vg/版。<ref>{{cite web|author=moot ''!Ep8pui8Vw2''|date=2012-02-16|url=http://archive.foolz.us/v/thread/129777358|title=Introducing /vg/ - Video Game Generals|website=4chan /v/ (檔案在foolz)|language=en|access-date=2012-08-17|archive-date=2022-03-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220304013317/http://archive.foolz.us/v/thread/129777358}}</ref>

4chan許多的有名事件或網絡爆紅是從/v/開始的。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gizmodo.co.uk/2015/02/everything-you-need-to-know-about-the-rickroll-everyones-favourite-internet-prank/|title=Everything You Need to Know About the Rickroll – The Internet's Favourite Prank|author=Spencer Hart|date=2015-02-06|website=Gizmodo|language=en|quote=May 2007 brought the first known instance of 'Rickrolling'. In 4chan's video game forum, /v/, a user posted a mirror-link to the first Grand Theft Auto IV trailer|accessdate=2015-09-16|archive-date=2015-09-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150908034105/http://www.gizmodo.co.uk/2015/02/everything-you-need-to-know-about-the-rickroll-everyones-favourite-internet-prank/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theawl.com/2015/02/what-was-the-bro|title=The Secret of the Bro|author=Johannah King-Slutzky|date=2015-02-20|website=The Awl|language=en|quote=The brofist was eventually popularized on /v/, 4Chan’s videogames sub, where... people say the phrase ‘PUT UP YOUR BROFIST.’ to act like they have a ‘network’ of friends|access-date=2015-09-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150907162631/http://www.theawl.com/2015/02/what-was-the-bro|archive-date=2015-09-07|dead-url=yes}}</ref>[[GamerGate|GamerGate]]事件剛開始在/v/啟動，可是由於一些關於管理員的爭議，大部分支持GamerGate的用戶為了繼續活動移到[[8chan|8chan]]。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.forbes.com/sites/erikkain/2014/09/04/gamergate-a-closer-look-at-the-controversy-sweeping-video-games/|title=GamerGate: A Closer Look At The Controversy Sweeping Video Games|author=Erik Kain|date=2014-09-04|website=[[福布斯|福布斯]]|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140905055813/http://www.forbes.com/sites/erikkain/2014/09/04/gamergate-a-closer-look-at-the-controversy-sweeping-video-games/|archive-date=2014-09-05|access-date=2015-09-16|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Chen">{{cite web|last=Chen|first=Adrian|date=2014-10-27|url=http://nymag.com/daily/intelligencer/2014/10/gamergate-supporters-party-at-strip-club.html|title=Gamergate Supporters Partied at a Strip Club This Weekend|work=[[紐約_(雜誌)|紐約雜誌]]|language=en|accessdate=2015-09-16|archive-date=2014-11-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141101085046/http://nymag.com/daily/intelligencer/2014/10/gamergate-supporters-party-at-strip-club.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>從2011年開始，/vp/版開始製造一個滑稽模仿版本神奇寶貝遊戲，叫做「Pokémon Sage」（神奇寶貝 下げ版）。<ref>{{cite web|date=2014-06-25|url=http://www.dualshockers.com/2014/06/25/4chans-project-pokemon-sage-and-why-you-should-be-playing-it/|title=4chan’s Project Pokémon Sage and Why You Should Be Playing It|website=DualShockers|language=en|accessdate=2014-07-01|archive-date=2014-06-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140629131803/http://www.dualshockers.com/2014/06/25/4chans-project-pokemon-sage-and-why-you-should-be-playing-it/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== /jp/ ===
[[File:Marisa_get_out_of_jp.png|thumb]]叫外來用户「滾出/jp/」。這圖片常被轉貼于/jp/。]]
