/jp/版（Otaku Culture，日本御宅族文化）是討論御宅族相关話題的貼圖版。<ref name=rulesib/>在2008年前，有些人在/a/版常常贴關於[[東方Project|東方Project]]，[[視覺小說|視覺小說]]和[[同人遊戲|同人遊戲]]的内容，由于這些話題跟動畫漫畫無關，大部分的/a/版民对此也有所抱怨。有鉴于此，克里斯托弗·普尔把/a/版分成兩半：/a/版專門討論動漫，/jp/討論其他话题，并以「Japan/General」（日本／一般性讨论）为版名，<ref>{{cite web|author=moot ''!Ep8pui8Vw2''|date=2008-02-20|url=http://cerealexperiments.com/moot.jpg|title=RE: /a/ vs. /jp/ (Screencap of /a/ post No.9743814)|archive-url=https://archive.is/20120714063108/http://cerealexperiments.com/moot.jpg|archive-date=2012-07-14|accessdate=2012-06-02|dead-url=no}}</ref>但后来/jp/版民又抱怨經常有外來人贴無關的日本社會內容，再將版名改成「Otaku Culture」。 /jp/版的话题有[[輕小說|輕小說]]、[[視覺小說|視覺小說]]、[[美少女遊戲|美少女遊戲]]、[[日本成人遊戲|日本成人遊戲]]、[[同人_(ACG)|同人]]文化、[[東方Project|東方Project]]、[[VOCALOID|VOCALOID]]、[[同人遊戲|同人遊戲]]、[[同人音樂|同人音樂]]、[[同人誌|同人誌]]、美少女[[人形|人形]]、[[尼特族|NEET]]生活、[[隱蔽青年|隱蔽青年]]問題等等。<ref>{{cite web|author=''Anonymous ## Mod'' (4chan管理员)|date=2012-08-10|url=http://archive.foolz.us/jp/thread/9549154|title=No.9549154 - /jp/ ("The new guidelines of what is acceptable on /jp/" sticky)|website=4chan (檔案在foolz)|language=en}}{{Dead link|date=2018年8月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} ([http://fuuka.warosu.org/jp/thread/9549154 warosu檔案])</ref>

4chan上眾所周知/jp/版民經常對版外人有敵意。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cerealexperiments.com/jprules.php|title=/jp/ Guidelines|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/66E5VGg5p?url=http://cerealexperiments.com/jprules.php|archive-date=2012-03-17|language=en|access-date=2012-03-17|dead-url=yes}}</ref>/jp/版民为自己有一個較小的網絡社區而自豪，因此如果有外來人发主题，版上的標準回應就是「get out of /jp/」（滾出/jp/）。/jp/的社區也发起过很多4chan以外的項目，如各种IRC頻道及/jp/版讨论檔案。{{notetag|4chan的/a/版与/jp/版有站外的自动讨论檔案，存檔网址为[http://archive.foolz.us/jp/ 这里 (Foolz)]和[http://fuuka.warosu.org/jp/ 这里 (Warosu)]。这些檔案网站全由版民自行建立，跟4chan的員工无关。许多4chan貼圖版存檔站使用基于[[Perl|Perl]]的[[开源软件|开源软件]][http://code.google.com/p/fuuka/ fuuka]（Yotsuba archiver）或其衍生软件抓取页面进行存档，如foolz存檔站所用即是基于[[PHP|PHP]]的fuuka衍生软件[https://github.com/FoolCode/FoolFuuka FoOlFuuka]。fuuka软件起初是为easymodo檔案网站编写的（此网站已停止运行）；关于檔案网站的历史，请看[http://www.webcitation.org/6B8lzjTjE 这里]。}}

=== /pol/ ===
[[File:4chan_-pol-_logo.png|thumb]]
/pol/版（Politics，政治）是討論政治與新聞的貼圖版。<ref name=rulesib/>剛開始這版本來在/n/，名为「News」（新聞版），但因版上大部分討論与種族歧視有關，结果全版被克里斯托弗·普尔刪除。在收到大量的骚扰郵件之後于/new/重建新聞版，并特地声明說若/new/再度成為一個種族歧視發言版，他會再度刪版，结果因此/new/版在2011年1月又被刪除。<ref name=newremove>{{cite web|date=2011-01-19|author=moot|url=http://content.4chan.org/tmp/r9knew.txt|title=Why were /r9k/ and /new/ removed?|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6159jR9pC?url=http://content.4chan.org/tmp/r9knew.txt|archive-date=2011-08-20|language=en|access-date=2012-03-20|dead-url=yes}}</ref>可是在2011年8月21日，moot向当时的/new/版民道歉：他谈到他曾批評过标榜言论自由的[[Encyclopedia_Dramatica|Encyclopedia Dramatica]]一站的創建者，指其毫无预警就關閉網站的行为忽视社群并妨碍了言论自由，但这次却發現自己在/new/的事情上也犯了同樣的錯誤——之後，moot于/pol/重建新闻版。<ref name=beyond/><ref>{{cite web|author=moot ''!Ep8pui8Vw2''|date=2011-10-23|url=http://www.webcitation.org/62dybAZ9z|title=Welcome back, robots|website=4chan /r9k/. (WebCite archive)|language=en|accessdate=2012-03-20|archive-date=2012-12-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121211041041/http://www.webcitation.org/62dybAZ9z|dead-url=no}}</ref>

許多的/pol/版民與當年的/new/版民有共同的特徵，其倾向包括[[種族主義|種族主義]]，[[種族歧視|種族歧視]]，反非洲人主義，[[反猶太主義|反猶太主義]]，[[否认犹太人大屠杀|否認納粹大屠殺]]，[[美國例外論|美國民族主義]]等等，因而/pol/版的許多話題与美國黑人犯罪率與猶太陰謀相关。雖然/pol/版民的政見繁雜，但总体来说[[右翼政治|右翼政治]]内容数量多，克里斯托弗·普尔也曾將/new/跟一個[[白人優越主義|白人優越主義]]的網站——「{{link-en|风暴前线|Stormfront (website)}}」相提並論。<ref name=newremove/>

各种西方媒体，例如《華盛頓郵報》曾經把/pol/形容成一個種族歧視或性別歧視的討論區，而且也包含[[新納粹主義|新納粹主義]]的情緒。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-intersect/wp/2014/09/25/absolutely-everything-you-need-to-know-to-understand-4chan-the-internets-own-bogeyman/|title=Absolutely everything you need to know to understand 4chan, the Internet’s own bogeyman|publisher=[[华盛顿邮报|华盛顿邮报]]|date=2014-09-25|accessdate=2015-07-17|language=en|archive-date=2015-07-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150722112859/http://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-intersect/wp/2014/09/25/absolutely-everything-you-need-to-know-to-understand-4chan-the-internets-own-bogeyman/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="auto2">{{cite web|url=http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2015/06/29/dylann-roof-4chan-and-the-new-online-racism.html|title=Dylann Roof, 4chan, and the New Online Racism|publisher=The Daily Beast|date=2015-06-29|accessdate=2015-07-17|language=en|archive-date=2015-07-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150715112056/http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2015/06/29/dylann-roof-4chan-and-the-new-online-racism.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="auto3">{{cite web|url=http://www.dailydot.com/lifestyle/4chan-end-fathers-day/|title=#EndFathersDay is the work of 4chan, not feminists|publisher=The Daily Dot|date=2014-10-08|accessdate=2015-07-17|language=en|archive-date=2015-06-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150629045924/http://www.dailydot.com/lifestyle/4chan-end-fathers-day/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vocativ.com/usa/race/4chan-deehubs/|title=4chan Trolls Take Over Electronic Billboard, Racism Ensues|publisher=Vocativ|date=2014-12-07|accessdate=2015-07-17|language=en|archive-date=2018-01-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180111165857/https://www.vocativ.com/usa/race/4chan-deehubs/|dead-url=no}}</ref>[[南方贫困法律中心|南方贫困法律中心]]認為各種白人優越主義網站經常仿真/pol/版的特制談話風格——其中的《{{link-en|每日風暴|The Daily Stormer}}》也承認這一點。<ref name="auto2"/>2012年[[特雷沃恩·馬丁命案|特雷沃恩·馬丁命案]]時，一些黑客把特雷沃恩的[[社会化媒体|社會媒體]]帳戶信息在/pol/上公開。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nymag.com/daily/intelligencer/2012/03/white-supremacist-claims-to-have-hacked-trayvon-martins-email-social-media-accounts.html|title=White Supremacist Claims to Have Hacked Trayvon Martin’s Email, Social Media Accounts|publisher=[[紐約客|紐約客]]|date=2012-03-29|accessdate=2015-07-17|language=en|archive-date=2015-07-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150722020322/http://nymag.com/daily/intelligencer/2012/03/white-supremacist-claims-to-have-hacked-trayvon-martins-email-social-media-accounts.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://thelede.blogs.nytimes.com/2012/03/29/bloggers-cherry-pick-from-social-media-to-cast-trayvon-martin-as-a-menace/|title=Bloggers Cherry-Pick From Social Media to Cast Trayvon Martin as a Menace|publisher=[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]|date=2012-03-29|accessdate=2015-07-17|language=en|archive-date=2015-09-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150911052521/http://thelede.blogs.nytimes.com/2012/03/29/bloggers-cherry-pick-from-social-media-to-cast-trayvon-martin-as-a-menace/|dead-url=no}}</ref>版民也曾經引起過各種[[反阿拉伯主義|反阿拉伯]]，[[反女權主義|反女權]]和[[跨性別恐懼症|反跨性別]]的[[Twitter|Twitter]]運動。<ref name="auto3"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://motherboard.vice.com/blog/trolls-4chan-online-feminism-women-of-color|title=What the Internet's Most Infamous Trolls Tell Us About Online Feminism|publisher=[[Vice媒体|Vice媒体]]|date=2014-06-20|accessdate=2015-07-17|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161231014510/https://motherboard.vice.com/blog/trolls-4chan-online-feminism-women-of-color|archive-date=2016-12-31|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://mic.com/articles/118862/trolls-are-paying-twitter-to-promote-hate-speech-and-there-s-nothing-stopping-them|title=Trolls Are Paying Twitter to Promote Hate Speech — And There's Nothing Stopping Them|publisher=Mic|date=2015-05-20|accessdate=2015-07-17|language=en|archive-date=2015-07-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150721184019/http://mic.com/articles/11886